Vice President Harris met with members of the Texas State Senate and Texas House of Representatives to discuss the restrictive voting measures in Texas and the importance of defending the right to vote. They talked about the potential consequences of denying people the right to vote, such as the denial of healthcare and underfunding education. They also emphasized the need to build diverse coalitions around common values and thanked the Vice President for her efforts to protect voting rights. In recent weeks, Vice President Harris has been engaging with local and national leaders on voting rights, and her future work will focus on educating the American people, building coalitions, advancing federal legislation, registering voters, and advocating for democratic principles worldwide. The Biden-Harris Administration is committed to protecting the right to vote and ensuring that every vote is counted through a transparent process.